The &amp;lt;A&amp;gt; tag is not valid within an &amp;lt;OPTION&amp;gt; tag. The only content allowed between &amp;lt;OPTION&amp;gt; tags is text. [HTML Elements Reference][1] That&#39;s why your selector isn&#39;t finding that element.

Instead of storing the video ID in the &amp;lt;A&amp;gt; tag in the **name** attribute, simply set the **value** of each &amp;lt;OPTION&amp;gt; to that ID. Then the **val()** of the entire &amp;lt;SELECT&amp;gt; becomes that video ID when changed. Here&#39;s my version of that section of markup:

    &lt;div class=&quot;select_div_container&quot;&gt;
    &lt;select class=&quot;dropped&quot; style=&quot;width: 100%;&quot;&gt;
        &lt;option value=&quot;&quot; selected disabled hidden&gt;Select a Training Video&lt;/option&gt;
        &lt;optgroup label=&quot;DROPPER&quot;&gt;
            &lt;option value=&quot;video_01&quot;&gt;VIDEO #1&lt;/option&gt;
            &lt;option value=&quot;video_02&quot;&gt;VIDEO #2&lt;/option&gt;
        &lt;/optgroup&gt;
    &lt;/select&gt;
    &lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;select_div_desc&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;video_span video_01&quot;&gt;VIDEO #1 DESCRIPTION&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;video_span video_02&quot;&gt;VIDEO #2 DESCRIPTION&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

And here&#39;s how I modified the JavaScript:

     $(&quot;.dropped&quot;).change(function()
     {
         var videoId = $(this).val();
         $(&quot;.video_iframe, .video_span&quot;).hide();
         $(&quot;#&quot; + videoId + &quot;, .&quot; + videoId).show(&quot;slow&quot;);
